  "stage": {
    "id": "applications_and_impact",
    "stageNumber": 5,
    "title": "Applications and Impact",
    "roomWidth": 20,
    "roomHeight": 15,
    "concepts": [
      {
        "id": "machine_translation",
        "title": "Neural Machine Translation",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- State-of-the-art BLEU scores\n- WMT 2014 benchmarks\n- Single model beats ensembles\n\nThe Transformer's debut application was machine translation, and the results were stunning. On WMT 2014 English-to-German, it achieved 28.4 BLEU—improving the previous best by more than 2 points. On English-to-French: 41.8 BLEU.\n\nWhat made this remarkable: a single Transformer model outperformed ensembles of the previous best models. It achieved this while training in a fraction of the time.\n\nThis was the moment the NLP community realized attention-only architectures weren't just theoretically interesting—they were practically superior. The race to scale Transformers had begun.",
        "position": {
          "x": 7,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "constituency_parsing",
        "title": "Constituency Parsing Transfer",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- Generalization to parsing\n- Limited task-specific tuning\n- Architecture versatility\n\nTo show the Transformer wasn't just a translation trick, Vaswani et al. applied it to English constituency parsing—predicting the grammatical structure of sentences as trees.\n\nWith minimal task-specific tuning, the Transformer achieved competitive results with state-of-the-art parsers that had been refined for years. This demonstrated the architecture's versatility: the same attention-based design that excels at translation also works for parsing.\n\nThis finding foreshadowed the era of foundation models: one architecture, pre-trained at scale, adapted to many tasks. BERT, GPT, and their descendants all build on this Transformer foundation.",
        "position": {
          "x": 11,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      }
    ],
    "quiz": {
      "id": "quiz-stage-5",
      "question": "What did the constituency parsing experiments demonstrate about the Transformer? Answer with a number.",
      "type": "multiple-choice",
      "options": [
        "It only works for translation tasks",
        "It can generalize to other structured prediction tasks",
        "It requires extensive task-specific modifications"
      ],
      "correctAnswer": "It can generalize to other structured prediction tasks",
